===Noun===
'''placenta''' (plural: '''[[placentae]]''' or '''[[placentas]]''')

# {{anatomy}} A vascular organ in [[mammal]]s, except [[monotreme]]s and [[marsupial]]s, present only in the female during [[gestation]]. It supplies food and oxygen from the mother to the [[foetus]], and passes back waste. It is implanted in the wall of the [[uterus]] and links to the [[foetus]] through the [[umbilical cord]]. It is expelled after birth.
# {{botany}} In flowering plants, the part of the [[ovary]] where [[ovule]]s develop; in non-flowering plants where the [[spore]]s develop.

